COMPONENT NAME:RKM Siebel EIM MSSQL
AUTHOR: Oracle
Description : - Reverse Knowledge Module - Reverse-engineering knowledge module for Siebel EIM (Enterprise Integration Manager) tables. - Projects could be reversed as sub-models (set the Option "Use project" to yes). - EIM tables are reversed as datastores with their columns and their constraints (Primary Keys).
Restrictions : - This KM works only for Siebel on Microsoft SQL Server

Mask used to filter the projects to be reverse-engineered. '%' returns all the projects.
Sample projects' names: EIM Accounts and Quotes EIM Activity EIM Administrative EIM Agreement EIM Asset Management EIM CTI EIM Call Script EIM Contact EIM Employee and Position EIM Field Service Inventory EIM Field Service Repair EIM Forecasts EIM Incentive Compensation EIM Interface Table 20C EIM Invoice EIM Marketing Campaign EIM Marketing Development Funds EIM Marketing Encyclopedia EIM Misc EIM Opportunity EIM Order Life Cycle EIM Personal Financial Review EIM Pricing EIM Products and Product Lines EIM Professional Services EIM Reference Data EIM Service Request EIM Siebel Interactive EIM Siebel Server EIM Territory EIM Workflow Manager EIM eTraining

select distinct p.ROW_ID SMOD_CODE, p.NAME SMOD_NAME from <%=odiRef.getObjectName("S_PROJECT")%> p inner join <%=odiRef.getObjectName("S_REPOSITORY")%> r on r.ROW_ID = p.REPOSITORY_ID and r.NAME = '<%=odiRef.getOption("REPOSITORY")%>' where p.NAME like 'EIM%' and p.NAME like '<%=odiRef.getOption("PROJECT_NAME")%>%'

insert into SNP_REV_TABLE (MOD_GUID, TABLE_NAME, RES_NAME, TABLE_ALIAS, TABLE_TYPE, TABLE_DESC_C, IND_SHOW,SMOD_CODE) values ('<%=odiRef.getModel("GLOBAL_ID")%>', :TABLE_NAME, :RES_NAME, :TABLE_ALIAS, 'T', :TABLE_DESC, '1',:SMOD_CODE)

select distinct t.NAME TABLE_NAME, t.NAME RES_NAME, substring(t.NAME,1,10) TABLE_ALIAS, t.DESC_TEXT TABLE_DESC, 0 R_COUNT, <% if ("1".equals(odiRef.getOption("USE_PROJECT"))) { %> t.PROJECT_ID <% } else { %> '' <% } %> SMOD_CODE from <%=odiRef.getObjectName("S_TABLE")%> t inner join <%=odiRef.getObjectName("S_PROJECT")%> p on t.PROJECT_ID = p.ROW_ID and p.NAME like '<%=odiRef.getOption("PROJECT_NAME")%>' and p.NAME like 'EIM%' inner join <%=odiRef.getObjectName("S_REPOSITORY")%> r on r.ROW_ID = t.REPOSITORY_ID and r.NAME = '<%=odiRef.getOption("REPOSITORY")%>' where t.TYPE= 'Interface' and t.NAME like '<%=odiRef.getModel("REV_OBJ_PATT")%>%'

insert into SNP_REV_COL ( MOD_GUID, TABLE_NAME, COL_NAME, DT_DRIVER, COL_DESC_C,COL_HEADING, POS, LONGC, SCALEC, COL_MANDATORY, CHECK_STAT, CHECK_FLOW) values ( '<%=odiRef.getModel("GLOBAL_ID")%>', :TABLE_NAME, :COL_NAME, :DT_DRIVER, :COL_DESC, :COL_HEADING, :POS, :LONGC, :SCALEC, :COL_MANDATORY, '0', '1')

select t.NAME TABLE_NAME, C.NAME COL_NAME, substring(C.DESC_TEXT,1,35) COL_HEADING, C.DESC_TEXT COL_DESC, bdd.DATA_TYPE DT_DRIVER, case when bdd.DATA_TYPE ='numeric' then bdd.NUMERIC_PRECISION else bdd.CHARACTER_MAXIMUM_LENGTH end LONGC, bdd.NUMERIC_SCALE SCALEC, 0 COL_MANDATORY, bdd.ORDINAL_POSITION POS from <%=odiRef.getObjectName("S_TABLE")%> t inner join <%=odiRef.getObjectName("S_COLUMN")%> C on t.ROW_ID = C.TBL_ID and C.TYPE not like 'IFMGR%' inner join INFORMATION_SCHEMA.COLUMNS bdd on C.NAME=bdd.COLUMN_NAME and t.NAME=bdd.TABLE_NAME and bdd.TABLE_CATALOG = '<%=odiRef.getModel("CATALOG_NAME")%>' inner join <%=odiRef.getObjectName("S_PROJECT")%> p on t.PROJECT_ID = p.ROW_ID and p.NAME like '<%=odiRef.getOption("PROJECT_NAME")%>' and p.NAME like 'EIM%' inner join <%=odiRef.getObjectName("S_REPOSITORY")%> r on r.ROW_ID = t.REPOSITORY_ID and r.NAME = '<%=odiRef.getOption("REPOSITORY")%>' where t.TYPE = 'Interface' and t.NAME like '<%=odiRef.getModel("REV_OBJ_PATT")%>%'

insert into SNP_REV_KEY (MOD_GUID, TABLE_NAME, KEY_NAME, CONS_TYPE, IND_ACTIVE, CHECK_FLOW, CHECK_STAT) Values ('<%=odiRef.getModel("GLOBAL_ID")%>', :TABLE_NAME, :KEY_NAME, :CONS_TYPE, '1', '1', '1' )

select tbl.NAME TABLE_NAME, 'PK' CONS_TYPE, idx.NAME KEY_NAME
from <%=odiRef.getObjectName("S_PROJECT")%> proj, <%=odiRef.getObjectName("S_INDEX")%> idx, <%=odiRef.getObjectName("S_TABLE")%> tbl
where proj.ROW_ID=tbl.PROJECT_ID and tbl.NAME like '<%=odiRef.getModel("REV_OBJ_PATT")%>%' and proj.NAME like '<%=odiRef.getOption("PROJECT_NAME")%>%' and tbl.ROW_ID=idx.TBL_ID and idx.ISUNIQUE='Y'
insert into SNP_REV_KEY_COL ( MOD_GUID, TABLE_NAME, KEY_NAME, COL_NAME, POS) Values ('<%=odiRef.getModel("GLOBAL_ID")%>', :TABLE_NAME, :KEY_NAME, :COL_NAME, :POS)

select tbl.NAME TABLE_NAME, 'PK' CONS_TYPE, idx.NAME KEY_NAME, idx_c.COL_POSTN POS, col.NAME COL_NAME
from <%=odiRef.getObjectName("S_PROJECT")%> proj, <%=odiRef.getObjectName("S_INDEX")%> idx, <%=odiRef.getObjectName("S_INDEX_COLUMN")%> idx_c , <%=odiRef.getObjectName("S_TABLE")%> tbl, <%=odiRef.getObjectName("S_COLUMN")%> col
where proj.ROW_ID=tbl.PROJECT_ID and tbl.NAME like '<%=odiRef.getModel("REV_OBJ_PATT")%>%' and proj.NAME like '<%=odiRef.getOption("PROJECT_NAME")%>%' and tbl.ROW_ID=idx.TBL_ID and col.ROW_ID=idx_c.COL_ID and idx.ROW_ID=idx_c.INDEX_ID and idx.ISUNIQUE='Y'

<% if (odiRef.getOption ("REPOSITORY").length() ==0) { %> raise OdiKMException("ODIKM-STDKM-10000", "ODIKM-STDKM-10000: Invalid value \"{0}\" for option \"REPOSITORY\"",["<%=odiRef.getOption ("REPOSITORY")%>"]) <%}%>
